### English Title:
Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu Addresses Hostage Situation and Ongoing Conflict in Gaza

### English Text Summary:
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu stated in a televised speech that Israel is in a "critical phase of the battle" in Gaza, emphasizing his commitment to returning all hostages without yielding to Hamas's demands. He noted that Hamas rejected a proposal to release half of the hostages in exchange for a ceasefire. Netanyahu's remarks coincided with protests in Tel Aviv calling for a deal to secure the release of all hostages. Meanwhile, the Israeli military reported casualties among its soldiers and significant civilian casualties in Gaza due to ongoing airstrikes. The humanitarian situation in Gaza is dire, with reports of severe shortages of food and medical supplies. Hamas has expressed its willingness to negotiate a prisoner exchange for a ceasefire, while Turkey's intelligence chief met with Hamas leaders to discuss humanitarian aid.

